  "body": "Hi there,\r\nI follow sync 4-5 days and I see big delay between etherscan and my node status.\r\nMy last line is:\r\nINFO [01-21|11:14:52] Imported new chain segment               blocks=2 txs=427 mgas=11.331 elapsed=58.490s  mgasps=0.194 number=4944709 hash=fe4694â€¦01d917\r\n\r\nBut the last block in ehtersan is 'LAST BLOCK 4946058'\r\nDifference is 1349 blocks.\r\nHow I can make faster this sync to actual block without remove all db and sync with fast?\r\n\r\nmy actual geth command:\r\ngeth --rpc --rpcaddr \"127.0.0.1\" --cache \"512\" --maxpeers 100 --rpcapi \"personal,eth,net,web3\" console\r\n\r\nI check with cache 2048, but result is the same\r\n\r\nIs something wrong with geth?\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Geth/v1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d/linux-amd64/go1.9`\r\nOS & Version: Linux Ubuntu 16.04\r\n",
